reviews.text: It is normally easy to get a table even during lunch time, so you can kind of guess how this restaurant is. They do have good variety of dim sum, but food quality is very average. More importantly, in Hong Kong, most restaurants change 10% service charge, however, here they charge 12%.

We stumbled upon this restaurant while searching for breakfast one morning. I believe we were the only tourists in the place which made our experience all the more enjoyable. As for the food, it was one of the best meals we had during our 3 week vacation. So delicious we came back a second time. I do not know the proper names of the dishes we had but they included steamed BBQ pork buns, shrimp dumplings, sticky rice, some kind of steamed sweet honey cake, and this delicious milky mango pudding. Yum!
Food is so-so. Staff doesn't listen to customer orders and overcharges customers.
Had a local friend take us here.  Delicious dim sum with good service. They have a rough translated English menu since we only know English. They take credit cards which is also nice.

Used to be a regular place. Popped in today. Quality was so so. Biggest surprise - the bill. Two people for sum ... $600?!? They said they'd changed their policy. Our fault for not reading the fine print, but we're not going back there. Not even close to worth it.

reviews.text: Place where almost all customers seem to be local, I couldn't find any westerners there. Prices are reasonable and volume of food served is generous. The menu and ordering system are quite confusing, and the staff can't really speak English, but everyone being of good will, you get about what you wish for, eventually. I especially recommend the mango pudding dessert, it doesn't look beautiful, but it tastes like the real thing. The restaurant furniture and tableware is quite worn out, but functional. Decoration is a little too much, a little too old, but not horrible. The whole place is just one big busy room with TV on the walls , it can become noisy.
Food is not bad. However the place gets very packed and is kind of chaotic. Best to go non peak hours.
Located juz between Central & Sheung Wan,  foods are nice well presented
Cheap and cheerful dim sum in Central....40% off before 11AM
Fresh dimsums, steam after orders placed, so can take little longer time...

地方大，服务差，服务員喜欢左指右指，取位時讲明有輪椅，便坐六人桌，後又指去八人桌，最後連輪椅只坐五人，但结賬收六人茶錢，16元—位。我覚得不是收几位的問題，是玩茶客問題，請大家留意！

無服務。正一劈場(劏客)。早茶10點後收正價。當日點了持價粥($19.80)，蝦腸(頂點)，义燒包(小點)埋單$160.00。原來頂點$63，小點$40。價錢都唔係問題，問題係腸粉粉漿未熟透，义燒包包皮濕到變軟，仲差過明星; 咁嘅價錢食酒店都食到啦。以前幫襯過其他分店(灣仔，天后，佐敦等)，一般金御只係中價酒樓，估咁到中環係劈場。咁嘅價錢，咁嘅食物質素同咁嘅服務，絕對唔值。我唔介意俾多啲錢，但介意俾貴價食平嘢，俾人當水魚。不會再去。
食物一般，無甚特式，環境座位尚算舒適。中環價錢，偏貴。
